message.content:
cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on learning locomotion in modular robots, both in simulation and in the real world. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper compares two learning algorithms, Bayesian optimization and HyperNEAT, to learn the controllers for the modular robots. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as the paper mentions evolutionary robot systems where both morphologies and controllers evolve. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper deals with controlling the locomotion of modular robots with evolvable morphologies. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category as the paper uses machine learning algorithms to learn the controllers for the modular robots.
